---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | FindVolleyball" description="What FindVolleyball collects, why, and how to ask us about it.">
  <main class="privacy-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <p>
      FindVolleyball is a small, free, community-run project — this policy is written in plain language because
      that's what it actually is. If anything here is unclear, email
      <a href="mailto:robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com">robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com</a> and ask.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Account info:</strong> if you sign up, we store your email address (via email/password or Google
      sign-in). We never see or store your password — that's handled entirely by our auth provider, Supabase.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Listings you submit:</strong> the details you enter on the submission form (location, schedule, cost,
      skill level, contact link, optional photo, etc.) and which account submitted it.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Votes and reports:</strong> when you vote "still happening?" or report an issue on a listing, we
      store that action and any note you write, tied to the listing — not to your identity beyond your account ID.
    </p>

    <h2>Why we collect it</h2>
    <p>
      To run the map: showing listings, letting you submit and manage your own, reviewing submissions before they
      go public, and keeping listing data accurate over time via votes and reports. We don't use any of this for
      advertising, and we don't sell or share it with data brokers.
    </p>

    <h2>Who else sees it</h2>
    <p>
      We rely on a small set of third-party services to run FindVolleyball, each only seeing what it needs to do
      its job:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — database, authentication, and photo storage.</li>
      <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosting, plus privacy-friendly Web Analytics (page views only, no cookies, no cross-site tracking).</li>
      <li><strong>Google</strong> — only if you choose "Sign in with Google" instead of email/password.</li>
      <li><strong>OpenStreetMap / Nominatim</strong> — converts the address you submit into map coordinates. Only the address text is sent, not your account info.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If a listing's contact link points to Buy Me a Coffee, Meetup, or another external site, visiting it is
      covered by that site's own privacy policy, not this one.
    </p>

    <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
    <p>
      Listing, vote, and report data stays as long as the listing does. If you want your account and associated
      data deleted, email us and we'll take care of it.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>FindVolleyball isn't directed at children under 13, and we don't knowingly collect data from them.</p>

    <h2>Questions or requests</h2>
    <p>
      To access, correct, or delete your data, or if you have any other question about this policy, email
      <a href="mailto:robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com">robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-page {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 32rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;

    h1 {
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .updated {
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: #888;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 1.75rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    p,
    li {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
    }

    li + li {
      margin-top: 0.4rem;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      font-weight: 600;
    }
  }
</style>
